    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Triethanolamine (TEA) is a yellow viscous organic compound used as a surfactant and emulsifier. It is both an amine and a triol, a class of alcohols that have three hydroxyl groups per molecule.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
